fied to me some people that I'd be better off not interacting with.<br>
<br>
However, there is one thing I really don't like seeing in the soapbox: discussions on religion or politics.  Talking about why a certain religion is better than another, or one country's foreign policy, is something that is only going to ignite a flame war. I don't really think that either have a place in the FV soapbox.  There are plenty of other places to discuss those things.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying I mind the non-Everquest rants that sometimes go into the Soapbox, but it's one thing to complain about a stupid coworker, a stressful day, or something of that nature (which more people are likely to give you sympathy) than to bring up religion and politics (which seems to usually stir up a hornet's nest).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oligith>Oligith</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/untitled.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf of Many Faces</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/4/03 1:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=369.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/10869.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Most Overplayed Topics</span><hr size=1> Dang it Kuladen.  <br>
